## Hard rules (worth interrupting a change over)

<!-- The handful the team most wants enforced. Examples — keep the project's real ones: -->
- Descriptive names always; in `map`/`filter`/etc. use the singular. Rename
  cryptic identifiers in code you touch. ({{NAMING_STRICTNESS}})
- Never compare against a string literal where a domain enum exists; never show
  a raw enum key to a user — translate via {{LABEL_MAP_LOCATION}}.
- Never reach past the repository layer; never expose a persistence entity —
  map to a DTO.
- Concurrent writes go in a transaction; critical operations
  ({{CRITICAL_OPS}}) are idempotent.
- Never swallow an error; log with context and propagate or return typed.
- Line length: {{LINE_LENGTH}} (enforced by {{FORMATTER}}).
- Tests: fast = `{{FAST_TEST_CMD}}` (run before pushing), full =
  `{{FULL_TEST_CMD}}` (CI).

